{
 "_name": "s25_two_team_separation",
 "_desc": "OTHER-TEAM separation PROOF (the cross-team gate, exercised \u2014 not just code-read). TWO co-located teams on shared RF: Team-X {X1,X2,X3} team_id 0x11111111 in a chain X1-X2-X3 (no X1-X3), and Team-Y {Y1,Y2} team_id 0x22222222, positioned so Y1/Y2 HEAR the whole Team-X flood. X1 send_hash X3 (a 2-hop teammate) forces a TEAM-scoped H flood (X3 unheard -> no key cache -> the Plane 1 team H-locate). Team-Y receives that flood but MUST DROP it (the f.team_id / h.team_id gate): Y never relays (h_forward) or answers (h_resolved) Team-X's flood, and never id_binds a Team-X key. Proves team<->team separation the way s24 proves static<->team. (The wrong-team F-drop uses the identical handle_f_team gate and is covered by the native unit test; H is the sim-forcible flood.)",
 "simulation": {
  "duration_ms": 600000,
  "step_ms": 1,
  "warmup_ms": 0,
  "beacon_period_ms": 20000,
  "seed": 25,
  "node_startup_jitter_ms": 0,
  "radio": {
   "sf": 8,
   "bw": 62.5,
   "cr": 5,
   "max_packet_bytes": 255,
   "snr_coherence_ms": 0,
   "duty_cycle": 0.01
  }
 },
